This product is an independent, clean-room reimplementation. It was informed by
studying the *behaviour and patterns* of the reference projects listed below; no
source code was copied verbatim from any of them.

================================================================================
Reference projects studied (behaviour/patterns only)
================================================================================

* martindieser/InfoLegMCP  — https://github.com/martindieser/InfoLegMCP
  No explicit license (all rights reserved). We did NOT copy code. We reused only
  non-copyrightable facts about how the public InfoLEG service behaves (HTTP
  endpoints, form field names, the modo=1|2 semantics of verVinculos, the 5,000-row
  annex folder convention, and the official dataset column names).

* abenassi/argentina-data-mcp — https://github.com/abenassi/argentina-data-mcp
  PolyForm Noncommercial License. We did NOT copy code and do not reuse it in a
  commercial context. We reimplemented engineering patterns (dual auth, hot-reload
  API keys, recency-boosted ranking, data-freshness/health, scheduled collectors).

* voftec/InfoLeg-MCP — https://github.com/voftec/InfoLeg-MCP
  MIT License. Adapted ideas with attribution (original-vs-updated diff, boletín
  helpers, MCP prompts). NOTE: we deliberately do NOT reproduce its incorrect
  50,000-block annex-folder computation, nor its disabling of TLS verification.

